英文表达原则
1. Plain English
用简单、常见、自然的词。
```
✅ help        ❌ assist
✅ use         ❌ utilise
✅ about       ❌ regarding
✅ before      ❌ prior to
✅ because     ❌ due to the fact that
✅ if          ❌ in the event that
✅ need        ❌ require
✅ start       ❌ commence
```
2. 像人说话
英文应该可以直接发出去，不像公告、合同、客服模板或 AI 输出。
```
❌ I sincerely hope this message finds you well and does not cause any inconvenience.
✅ Hope you’re doing well. I wanted to ask a quick question.
```
3. 先说重点
中文可以铺垫很多，英文通常先说事。
```
❌ Sorry to bother you. I know you’re busy, and I was wondering if maybe when you have time...
✅ Could you take a look at this when you have a chance? No rush.
```
4. 礼貌但不卑微
请求别人时，要给对方空间，但不要把自己放得太低。
```
✅ No worries if not.
✅ Totally fine if that doesn’t work.
✅ If you have time, I’d really appreciate your thoughts.

❌ I’m so sorry to trouble you again.
❌ If it is not too much trouble for you, could you possibly...
```
5. 温和但明确
尤其是拒绝、催促、投诉、表达不同意见时，要清楚，不要绕到对方看不懂。
```
✅ I don’t think I can take this on right now.
✅ Just wanted to follow up in case this got buried.
✅ I see your point, but I’m not sure this solves the main issue.
```
6. 少用大词和空词
避免这些看起来“高级”但很空的词：
```
❌ wonderful opportunity
❌ valuable insights
❌ greatly appreciated
❌ seamless experience
❌ innovative solution
❌ empower users
```
除非场景真的需要，否则换成具体、自然的话。
7. 根据关系调整语气
同一个中文意思，可以有不同英文版本：
中文：你有空帮我看一下吗？
朋友：
```text
Could you take a quick look when you have time?
```
同事：
```text
Could you take a look when you get a chance? No rush.
```
老师：
```text
Would you be able to take a look when you have a moment?
```
客户：
```text
Could you review this when convenient and let us know if anything needs to be changed?
```
